humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: Based on the pathology report, 4 out of 7 assessed lymph nodes are positive for metastasis (Axillary 4/7). This corresponds to the N1 stage, as per New Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes (No/Total). The report does not mention any other factors that would modify the N stage, such as in-transit, satellite, or micrometastases in lymph nodes.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has 4 out of 7 axillary lymph nodes positive for metastasis (Axillary 4/7). This indicates a pathologic N1 stage. The extracapsular invasion, margins, and other details are not specified, but they are not required for determining the N stage in this case.
